captions.text: (screaming)
Scott: Hey guys, Scott here and welcome
to a new series that I like to call
Super Mega Fan Time.
Super Mega Fan Time.
I just named that on the spot.
This is what it's called.
We have committed, it is done.
Okay.
God, I'm so wobbly.
Oh jees, help, help!
All right, anyway.

Super Mega Fan Time, if
you guys are wondering,
is basically just kind of a series where
I take three different questions from all
of my social media sites whether it be

Twitter, Facebook,
Instagram, my other channel,
my vlogging channel.
Guys, go check out my vlogging channel.

So basically I will
take different questions
from all ...
What's the in the background?
(loud animal noise)
Uh.

So remember to basically
leave a bunch of comments
on my Instagram, my Facebook, my Twitter.

Make sure to follow them
all and also make sure
to leave a comment here because I check

every social media site
and, yeah, it's going
to be awesome.
But that's not all.

So every episode I actually
do a different challenge.
And I believe that this challenge is going

to be pretty epic, but
we'll get to the end
there pretty soon.

But, yeah, let's start
with some of the questions.
All right, lay them on me.

Voiceover: What do you
want to do in the future?

Scott: I think what I
want to do in the future

is probably work for
Funimation because ever since

I was a kid I used to always
watch, like, Dragonball Z

or Trigon or various other
kinds of, like, animes.

And I've always wanted
to be the super hero.

So I think probably
that's what I would do.
Voiceover: Where would you be
if it wasn't for YouTube?
Scott: Oh God.
So, yeah.

I think I've described
this a couple times before.

I actually didn't have,
like, one of the best
pasts ever and YouTube was kind of one of

the things that pulled
me out of my depression.
So I honestly can't say where I would
probably be without YouTube.
I know everything just got really serious.

Could someone put dramatic
music going on here,
just (high pitched sound).
All right, anyway.

I have no idea where I
would be without YouTube

because all of you guys
mean so much to me,
you have no idea.
So I don't know.
Like, Subway (chuckles).
Voiceover: What are you planning on doing
for your 10 million subscriber special?

Scott: So for my 10
million subscriber special
I plan on doing draw my life.
But I'm not going to be doing an average

draw my life, I want
to do something called
animate my life.

So I'm going to have sub
team up with me and we're
going to basically make a little animation
about my life.

It's not going to be,
like, animation animation

rather than just little
screenies and various
pictures of my life.

So it's been kind of a
hard thing to do because,
like I said before, I have not had
the best past ever.
But, yeah, we're trying to get it done.
Don't get me wrong.
We're like, it's in the works.

But it's taking a little
bit longer than expected.
So, yeah!

I guess that only leaves
the challenge now.

So we're going to cut
this up and we're going
to go jump into the lake and we'll see
what happens there.
But yeah, remember this is Washington.
We're right next to Canada.
So it's going to be a lot colder than
your average water.
So (hisses), not looking forward to this
actually, okay.
Oh, I really don't want to do this.
Bob: Well you kind of have to,
you already told them-
(splash)
Scott: I'm coming Bob!
(splash)
Bob: Holy cold!
Scott: Oh, oh it's so cold!
(high pitched screaming)
Oh, it's stinky!
(laughing)
(girl screaming)
Voiceover: Ah, no it's cold, no!
I hate you, no!
(screaming)
No, no, ah!
Scott: Okay.
But anyway guys.
Oh, that was something.
But anyway guys.
Make sure to leave a comment in either
my Twitter, my Facebook, my Instagram,
this video or whatever and if I see it,
then I may use it.
Also, make sure to leave a challenge down
below as well.
Because, God.
If everything's going to be like this
it's going to suck, man.
Bob: Yeah.
Scott: Woo, it's cold.
Bob: Get this video to 100,000 likes.
Scott: That'll be ...
Voiceover: Make sure it's mean.
Scott: Oh God.
But anyway guys, thank you so much for

watching and we'll see
you guys later, goodbye!
(techno music)
